name: InkSketchColour1
description:
Trained for SD 2.1. v2-1_768-ema-pruned.ckpt specifically.

Contains 16 vectors.

Creates colorized environment lineart. Trained on concept art images of interior environment lineart. Works okay with other subject matter, but has a tendency to skew image output towards objects with angular features/and or adds buildings to the scene.

2 Versions, Standard and subtle.

Subtle is the same embedding with the vector values lowered, which seems to have a different effect than turning down the token within the prompt (InkSketchcolour:0.5) for example. It preforms better on non-architectural subject matter.

Place late in prompt. Made to be mixed with other paintsyles. Pairs well with laxpeintv2, vray-render, cardstyle.

For best effect: <subject matter here> InkSketchColour1 <other paint effects here> InkSketchColour1Subtle

Repeating the token helps maintain the effect, otherwise the lineart tends to be lost.
